New council housing could be built on a former sea cadets site in Caterham.Tandridge District Council is set to submit a planning application for land it bought from the Ministry of Defence in 2023. Earlier plans showed the site at The Grove and Hawarden Road, which includes a former barracks, could be used for up to 16 homes.Council documents show they would all be family sized, with two to four bedrooms, and would be available at 70% of market rent.
They would be retained by the council and let to families in housing need.The project, including an extra Â£50,000 to fund it, is set to be discussed by the council on 18 June.
